  "bookId": 38,
  "firstAcquaintance": "The New Year has arrived, and Julen has changed into her battle outfit. \"A battle outfit?\" \"Yes.\" She nods firmly.",
  "personality": "Quiet, aloof, and somewhat reclusive. However, when it comes to lucky money, she shows an enthusiasm quite unlike her usual self.",
  "like": "Lucky money, good grown-ups",
  "familiarData": "The New Year has arrived - a day for everyone to relax and celebrate. Everyone, that is, except Julen, because this is the day she gets lucky money. She puts on her most battle-ready expression, transforming into the Lucky Money Oni who strikes directly at wallets.\nGreeting people on her own, serving tea to elders, and even knowing to wear shoes in public - is this really Julen?!\nOnly good children get lucky money, so on New Year's Day, Julen becomes a well-mannered, chore-loving good child. No adult can refuse to give lucky money to such a well-behaved Julen, and those who try... will be persuaded otherwise with a \"comfortable massage\" that leaves no room for argument.\nAs the outstanding Lucky Money Oni, she serves as the guild's mascot, wielding her sake bowl in her left hand to summon fortune, and her kanabo in her right hand to smash away all bad luck.",
